{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"baac19ac-b8fc-4bfe-8c51-d64c84aa2d89","content":"For a **.NET Web API**, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows/NTLM authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nFor **JWT bearer** auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7faf3a0e-83bd-4be2-b1be-2de313d2dd41","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context) or web development in general. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to look at files.\n\nActually, let me check if this is related to the repository context - there are dotnet plugins mentioned. But the user's question is general - they're asking about templates and authentication options for creating a web API project. This is a straightforward knowledge question.","outputTokens":377,"requestId":"A7C2:155537:167240D:18FB5CE:6A051DFF"},"id":"fdce8d04-d834-4f4e-b2fb-f93be5fc0058","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:57:45.927Z","parentId":"5d69d90a-0d37-4259-bf8b-4d164e3ed211"}
